name: deviceManagement_CreateUserExperienceAnalyticsBatteryHealthModelPerformance
description: Create new navigation property to userExperienceAnalyticsBatteryHealthModelPerformance for deviceManagement

$block: The user experience analytics battery health model performance entity contains battery related information for all unique device models in their organization.

$ul: **id**: The unique identifier for an entity. Read-only.
**activeDevices**: Number of active devices for that model. Valid values -2147483648 to 2147483647
**averageBatteryAgeInDays**: The mean of the battery age for all devices of a given model in a tenant. Unit in days. Valid values -2147483648 to 2147483647
**averageEstimatedRuntimeInMinutes**: The mean of the estimated runtimes on full charge for all devices of a given model. Unit in minutes. Valid values -2147483648 to 2147483647

**averageMaxCapacityPercentage**: The mean of the maximum capacity for all devices of a given model. Maximum capacity measures the full charge vs. design capacity for a device’s batteries.. Valid values -2147483648 to 2147483647
**model**: The model name of the device.
**modelBatteryHealthScore**: A weighted average of a model’s maximum capacity score and runtime estimate score. Values range from 0-100. Valid values -2147483648 to 2147483647
**client-request-id**: Client request Id as sent by the client application.
**request-id**: Request Id as tracked internally by the service
